definitions.definition: A set of non-physical psychological and social qualities that make one person distinct from another.
examples: The president has a unique personality .

definitions.definition: Charisma , or qualities that make a person stand out from the crowd.
examples: The best contestant shows most personality .

definitions.definition: A set of qualities that make something distinctive or interesting.
examples: His writing has a lot of personality .
This functional concrete building lacks personality .

definitions.definition: An assumed role or manner of behavior.
examples: In his final act, the comedian takes on a child's personality .

definitions.definition: A celebrity , especially one with a strong media presence (e.g. an actor , singer , or sports player).
examples: Johnny Carson was a respected television personality .

definitions.definition: Something said or written which refers to the person, conduct, etc., of some individual, especially something of a disparaging or offensive nature; personal remarks.
That quality of a law which concerns the condition, state, and capacity of persons.
A set of female breasts ; a rack ; ( also occasionally ) an individual breast.
examples: Whoa mama! That gal's got a fine... er, " personality ".
